\
The main program to run is main.m. But first, you must prepare data files and the Input_file.m script. Data files should be placed in the data folder. The file formats are described in Input_file.m \
\
You should modify (and probably rename) the Input_file.m script.  You can include one or more data sets. This file also specifies parameters that are to be fixed and parameters that are to be estimated as well as imposed bounds on parameters. Follow the instructions in Input_file.m. \
\
After preparing data and Input_file.m, run main.m to compute the MCMC inversion.  The script will compute approximate completion time. You do not need to run the inversion to completion. At any point you can terminate the inversion with Control-C. Outputs of the MCMC inversion are written to text files in the MCMC_output folder. \
\
After running main.m, you can visualize the results using plot_results.m.  This script produces some very simple plots. \
\
\
To illustrate the code, synthetic data sets are provided in the data folder and Input_file.m is set up to load the synthetic data. You should be able to run the synthetic inversion by simply executing main.m.\
